## 1. Project Overview

**HireX** is an enterprise hiring platform that enforces strict identity uniqueness:

- **One email → One account** (enforced at MongoDB level)
- **One face → One account** (enforced via ArcFace + Qdrant cosine similarity)

Every user who signs up must:
1. Pass an **active liveness challenge** (blink or head-turn detected by MediaPipe in the browser)
2. Pass an **anti-spoofing check** (MiniFASNet on the Python backend)
3. Have their face compared against all existing users via **512-dimensional ArcFace embeddings** stored in **Qdrant Cloud**
4. Verify their **email via a 6-digit OTP** (sent via SMTP)

Only after all four checks pass is a MongoDB user document created and a JWT issued.

