## 6. Service Setup & Running

All three services must run simultaneously for the full signup flow to work.

### 6.1 Frontend (Remix / React Router)

**Prerequisites:** Node.js 18+

```powershell
cd frontend
npm install        # already done — skip if node_modules exists
npm run dev        # starts at http://localhost:5173
```

**Available Scripts:**
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `npm run dev` | Development server with HMR |
| `npm run build` | Production build |
| `npm start` | Serve production build |

---

### 6.2 Backend (Express + TypeScript)

**Prerequisites:** Node.js 18+, MongoDB running locally on port 27017

```powershell
cd backend
npm install        # already done — skip if node_modules exists

# Fill in your .env values first!
npm run dev        # starts at http://localhost:5000 with nodemon auto-reload
```

**Available Scripts:**
| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `npm run dev` | Development with `nodemon` + `ts-node` |
| `npm run build` | Compile TypeScript → `dist/` |
| `npm start` | Run compiled JS from `dist/` (production) |

**MongoDB Setup (local):**
Make sure MongoDB is installed and the service is running:
```powershell
# Windows — if installed as a service
net start MongoDB

# Or start manually
mongod --dbpath C:\data\db
```
The database `hirex` and its collections are created automatically on first use.

---

### 6.3 Python FastAPI (ML Service)

**Prerequisites:** Python 3.10+, pip

```powershell
cd python

# 1. Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
# NOTE: First install downloads PyTorch + TensorFlow — may take 10-15 minutes

# 3. Fill in your python/.env values!

# 4. Start the server
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
# API docs at: http://localhost:8000/docs
```

> **Important — First Run:**
> On first startup, `DeepFace` will automatically download the **ArcFace model weights (~500MB)**
> to `~/.deepface/weights/`. This is a one-time download.
>
> The MiniFASNet anti-spoofing weights (~4MB) are downloaded from GitHub on first `/verify-liveness`
> call and cached in `python/models/silent_face/`.

